### Bug: Email Rollback Fails, UI/Backend Mismatch

<!-- **High Severity** -->

<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->
The rollback logic for `_onEmailArchive` and `_onEmailDelete` attempts to=
 re-insert an email using an `emailIndex` from the original list. After a=
n optimistic removal, this index is incorrect for the modified list, pote=
ntially misplacing the email or causing an index error. Additionally, `_o=
nEmailArchive` performs an optimistic UI update but lacks a backend imple=
mentation, leading to an inconsistent state where emails are removed from=
 the UI but not archived on the server.
<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->

<!-- LOCATIONS START
lib/presentation/blocs/mailbox/mailbox_bloc.dart#L515-L531
lib/presentation/blocs/mailbox/mailbox_bloc.dart#L566-L575
lib/presentation/blocs/mailbox/mailbox_bloc.dart#L433-L442
LOCATIONS END -->
